ViewTemplateBodyFilter Cascade Ordering

The `:cascade` filter run prefix evaluates step filters sequentially. If a third-party plugin's cascade filter has a bug (error, side effect), it can silently prevent ALL subsequent cascade filters from matching.

Symptom: your cascade filter works when tested alone but returns empty when run as part of the full chain:

```
<!-- Works alone -->
{{{ [<currentTiddler>] :cascade[[$:/my/cascade/filter]get[text]] }}}

<!-- Returns empty with all filters -->
{{{ [<currentTiddler>] :cascade[all[shadows+tiddlers]tag[$:/tags/ViewTemplateBodyFilter]!is[draft]get[text]] }}}
```

Known offenders: `flibbles/graph`, `wikilabs`, `EvidentlyCube/AutoComplete` cascade filters have been observed to break the chain in TW 5.3.8.

Fix: position your cascade filter FIRST, not last:

```
<!-- WRONG — last before default, vulnerable to broken earlier filters -->
list-before: $:/config/ViewTemplateBodyFilters/default

<!-- CORRECT — first in chain, runs before anything can break it -->
list-before: $:/config/ViewTemplateBodyFilters/testcase
```

Also: `all[current]` is redundant in `:cascade` step filters. The cascade prefix already passes the tiddler title as input to each step filter:

```
<!-- Redundant -->
[all[current]has[_thumbnail_uri]then[...]]

<!-- Cleaner — works the same in :cascade context -->
[has[_thumbnail_uri]then[...]]
```
